### Phase 2 — direct Judge0 smoke test
### Open the IAP tunnel first:  make judge0-tunnel
### Then run these top-to-bottom against the `local` env.

### 1. Metadata — confirms tunnel + Judge0 is up
GET {{judge0Url}}/about

### 2. Supported languages — populates the Phase 4 language dropdown
GET {{judge0Url}}/languages

### 3. Synchronous Python hello-world (waits for the result)
POST {{judge0Url}}/submissions?wait=true&base64_encoded=false&fields=stdout,stderr,status,time,memory,token
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "source_code": "print('Hello, CodeArena')",
  "language_id": 71,
  "stdin": ""
}

### 4. Async submission — returns a token; results fetched in step 5
POST {{judge0Url}}/submissions?base64_encoded=false
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "source_code": "name = input()\nprint(f'Hi {name}')",
  "language_id": 71,
  "stdin": "Alice"
}

> {%
    client.global.set("judge0Token", response.body.token);
%}

### 5. Poll for the async result (run a couple of times if status is "In Queue")
GET {{judge0Url}}/submissions/{{judge0Token}}?base64_encoded=false&fields=stdout,stderr,status,time,memory,token

### 6. Java hello-world — exercises a heavier compile path
POST {{judge0Url}}/submissions?wait=true&base64_encoded=false&fields=stdout,stderr,status,time,memory
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "source_code": "public class Main { public static void main(String[] a) { System.out.println(\"Hi from Java\"); } }",
  "language_id": 62,
  "stdin": ""
}

### 7. Intentional runtime error — should return RUNTIME_ERROR with stderr
POST {{judge0Url}}/submissions?wait=true&base64_encoded=false&fields=stdout,stderr,status,time,memory
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "source_code": "print(1/0)",
  "language_id": 71,
  "stdin": ""
}

### 8. Intentional compile error — should return COMPILATION_ERROR with compile_output
POST {{judge0Url}}/submissions?wait=true&base64_encoded=false&fields=stdout,stderr,compile_output,status,time,memory
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "source_code": "prit('typo')",
  "language_id": 71,
  "stdin": ""
}

### 9. Submission with expected_output match → ACCEPTED
POST {{judge0Url}}/submissions?wait=true&base64_encoded=false&fields=stdout,status,time,memory
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "source_code": "print(2 + 3)",
  "language_id": 71,
  "stdin": "",
  "expected_output": "5\n"
}

### 10. Same code, mismatched expected_output → WRONG_ANSWER
POST {{judge0Url}}/submissions?wait=true&base64_encoded=false&fields=stdout,status,time,memory
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "source_code": "print(2 + 3)",
  "language_id": 71,
  "stdin": "",
  "expected_output": "42\n"
}
